    <h3>Places to Visit</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>
            <strong>1. Sula Vineyards</strong>
            <p>Sula Vineyards is a popular winery in Nashik known for its picturesque vineyards and wine tasting tours. Visitors can explore the vineyards, learn about the wine-making process, and enjoy wine tasting sessions.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <strong>2. Trimbakeshwar Temple</strong>
            <p>Trimbakeshwar Temple is a renowned Hindu temple dedicated to Lord Shiva. It is one of the twelve Jyotirlingas and is located near the Brahmagiri hills in Nashik. The temple's architecture and spiritual significance attract devotees from around the country.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <strong>3. Pandavleni Caves</strong>
            <p>Pandavleni Caves, also known as Trirashmi Leni, are ancient rock-cut caves situated on a hilltop in Nashik. These caves date back to the 3rd century BCE and offer a glimpse into the Buddhist heritage of the region.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <strong>4. Saptashrungi Devi Temple</strong>
            <p>Saptashrungi Devi Temple is a famous Hindu temple dedicated to Goddess Durga. It is located on a hilltop and offers panoramic views of the surrounding valleys. The temple is a significant pilgrimage site and attracts devotees during Navratri.</p>
        </li>
    </ul>
    
